67.1	The_Passion_of_the_Christ	The Passion of the Christ	The Passion of the Christ (sometimes referred to as The Passion) is a 2004 American drama film directed by Mel Gibson and starring Jim Caviezel as Jesus Christ. It depicts the Passion of Jesus largely according to the New Testament Gospels of Matthew, Mark, Luke and John. It also draws on other devotional writings, such as those disputedly attributed to Anne Catherine Emmerich.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/61/Thepassionposterface-1-.jpg/215px-Thepassionposterface-1-.jpg
